FBIS3-54999 "drsov003_d_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 Regional Affairs Yeltsin Sends Telegram to Chuvashia President LD0501120494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0653 GMT 5 Jan 94 LD0501120494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valentina Ivanova] [Text] Cheboksary, 5 Jan -- Boris Yeltsin greeted Nikolay Fedorov on his election as Chuvashia's first president. "I am confident that you will proceed further with economic reforms for the sake of making the life of the Chuvash people dignified and that you will facilitate the strengthening of Russia's constitutional foundations. I look forward to carrying out constructive work together," emphasized the Russian Federation president in his telegram. Today SOVETSKAYA CHUVASHIA published the presidential greetings as the first message on a whole page of similar greetings which continue to arrive for the 35 year old former Russian Justice Minister Nikolay Fedorov, who was elected to Chuvashia's highest state post on New Year's eve.
